snippet: Less than 12 hours after a warning alarm roused two astronauts from their sleep, everything was back to normal, NASA said, and there were strong indications that the problem was a faulty computer card rather than an actual leak.
abstract: NASA says American and European crew members on International Space Station were evacuated to Russian area of station twice over concerns of possible ammonia leak that turned out to be faulty computer card.
lead_paragraph: Less than 12 hours after a warning alarm roused two astronauts from their sleep, everything was back to normal, NASA said, and there were strong indications that the problem was a faulty computer card rather than an actual leak.

headline.main: Space Station Crew Temporarily Moves to Russian Side Over Fears of Ammonia Leak
headline.print_headline: Leak Fears Prompt Space Station Shuffling
